                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6–1649</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Acting Secretary of State of a Conversation
                        With the President</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-16">June 16,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chou En</hi>-<hi rend="smallcaps">lai</hi> “<hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Démarche</hi>”</p>
                <p>I brought the President up to date with respect to the Chou En-lai <hi
                        rend="italic">Démarche</hi> and read to him the pertinent sections of our
                        reply.<note n="36" xml:id="d460fn36">See telegram No. 367, June 14, 5 p. m.,
                            <ref target="#pg_384">p. 384</ref>.</note> He approved this course of
                    action and directs us to be most careful not to indicate any softening toward
                    the Communists but to insist on judging their intentions by their actions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> E. <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
